# {{ project_name }} — Coding Conventions

This document defines coding standards, conventions, and best practices for this
codebase. It serves as the repo-wide baseline; scoped instructions and skills take
priority when they apply.

## Scope and Precedence

1. **Skills** (`.github/skills/`) — task-specific playbooks (highest specificity)
2. **Instructions** (`.github/instructions/`) — file-scoped rules for matching globs
3. **This file** — repo-wide baseline (lowest specificity)

If rules conflict, prefer the **most specific applicable scope**.

